id: pmc-7dm6
title: Fix release tag date drift in changelog checks
description: "npm run changelog:check -- --json regenerates the current package release heading with today's date instead of the existing release tag date when --release-version-from-package and --until-release-tag are used."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[3]: changelog,check,release
created_at: "2026-05-25T20:39:28.655Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-25T22:42:33.040Z"
author: codex
acceptance_criteria: "Release-context generation derives the release heading date from the existing release tag when no explicit --date is passed, and changelog:check passes."
reporter: codex
severity: medium
environment: pm-changelog main at 2026.5.24-15
repro_steps: "npm run changelog:check -- --json"
resolution: "Fixed in release-context, CLI, extension, and explicit --version handling: existing release tag timestamps now provide the default changelog heading date when a release tag can be resolved, while --until remains gated by --until-release-tag."
expected_result: Check mode reports changed=false when CHANGELOG.md already matches the package release tag.
actual_result: Check mode exits 1 with changed=true because the generated heading is 2026.5.24-15 - 2026-05-25 while the checked-in heading is 2026.5.24-15 - 2026-05-24.
fixed_version: 2026.5.25
component: release-context
comments[6]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-25T21:20:35.021Z",codex-active-continuation,"Followed up on PR review feedback after the initial fix: release tag timestamp is now resolved whenever a matching package release tag exists so the heading date is stable even without --until-release-tag, while --until remains gated by --until-release-tag. Expanded timestamp date parsing to accept T, space, or date-only separators. Added CLI coverage for package-version tag date derivation without limiting the release window. Verified npm test, npm run changelog:check -- --json, and npm run check."
  "2026-05-25T21:22:27.553Z",codex-active-continuation,"Post-rebase verification found the package-owned all-release-tags changelog check was stale on the updated 2026.5.25 main base. Regenerated CHANGELOG.md with npm run changelog:full -- --json and re-ran npm run changelog:check -- --json successfully (changed=false, itemCount=48)."
  "2026-05-25T21:24:47.048Z",codex-active-continuation,"CI parity follow-up: fetched origin tags locally and reproduced GitHub Actions changelog:check failure caused by the newly visible v2026.05.25 tag. Regenerated CHANGELOG.md with npm run changelog:full -- --json using the full tag set, then verified npm run changelog:check -- --json and npm run check pass."
  "2026-05-25T21:47:18.107Z",codex-active-continuation,"Addressed latest PR #13 Gemini feedback: explicit --version now triggers release-context lookup so matching git tags can provide the heading date even without --release-version-from-package/--since/--until flags; extension command now reads date/since/until through stringOption helper instead of direct type assertions. Added CLI regression coverage for explicit version tag heading dates. Verification: npm test (33 tests), npm run check, and npm run changelog:check -- --json."
  "2026-05-25T22:32:01.432Z",codex-active-continuation,"Addressed latest PR #13 Gemini feedback: release context now tolerates unresolved git timestamps (for shallow/partial clone environments) by treating unavailable release-tag timestamps as absent instead of failing, and full release-tag history headings now use the local timestamp date formatter to avoid timezone-induced date drift. Verification: npm test, npm run check, and npm run changelog:check -- --json."
  "2026-05-25T22:42:33.040Z",codex-active-continuation,"Addressed latest PR #13 review feedback after Gemini/Codex responses: release-context now uses the non-throwing git timestamp helper for previous-tag since derivation so shallow/partial clones degrade without aborting; extension option parsing now reads title through stringOption and reuses one parsed title value; extension date flag help now matches CLI tag-derived fallback wording. Verification after edits: npm test (33 tests), npm run check, npm run changelog:check -- --json (unchanged, itemCount=48)."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-25T20:41:05.751Z",codex,"Implemented release-context date propagation: existing release tag timestamp now supplies the generated heading date when --until-release-tag is used and --date is omitted."
